1
00:00:01,806 --> 00:00:08,109
This kind of horror was the almost daily portion of some people somewhere in the 1944 Battle of London.

2
00:00:09,771 --> 00:00:14,054
The phase ended with the capture of flying bomb sites such as this along the Channel Coast of France.

3
00:00:14,535 --> 00:00:20,998
The magnificent advance of the British and Canadians in northern France to Belgium ended this particular terror that flew by night and day.

4
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:23,400
Plans had been prepared long beforehand.

5
00:00:23,881 --> 00:00:29,344
Under the GOCC anti-aircraft command general Sir Frederick Pyle the defense was constantly improved.

6
00:00:29,928 --> 00:00:34,493
Och av 8000 flygbomb som lanserats mot oss, har inte mer än 2300 gått igenom kriget.

7
00:00:34,514 --> 00:00:40,439
Vår historia är berättad främst från perspektivet av antikrigsbombarna, som har samlat en stor del av döden.

8
00:00:41,841 --> 00:00:43,383
De kvinnorna är alla volontärer.

9
00:00:49,128 --> 00:00:50,331
Det gör oss alla stolta.

10
00:00:51,186 --> 00:00:54,429
Nothing can be said of the technical genius that went into the guns themselves.

11
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:56,470
That may be told after the war.

12
00:00:56,951 --> 00:01:01,454
But the work of the men and women of the gun sites on the flying bomb coast you can judge for yourself.

13
00:01:01,475 --> 00:01:05,718
The record days work have gone out of a total of 101.

14
00:01:05,737 --> 00:01:08,980
But many of the defenders lost their lives from the bombs they brought down.

15
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:07,127
Air Defence of Great Britain fighters joined in the hunt.

16
00:03:41,896 --> 00:03:45,501
Söderngland har haft en stor ordeel under de 80 dagarna efter D-dagen.

17
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:49,444
Men hur mycket större skulle det varit om de 8000 flygbombarna inte hade förstört 1560?

18
00:03:49,504 --> 00:03:53,169
Om kruven av krigskommanden inte hade skjutit ner 1900?

19
00:03:53,209 --> 00:03:55,972
Om kruven av ballonerna inte hade stått och förstört 279?

20
00:03:55,991 --> 00:03:58,814
Hur mycket värre skulle det ha varit?

21
00:04:04,324 --> 00:04:07,525
Many families have lost their lives and many more lost everything else.

22
00:04:07,784 --> 00:04:10,344
But London looks much the same today as it did before.

23
00:04:10,425 --> 00:04:14,586
What a grand job they did for us, the personnel of Air Defence of Great Britain.

24
00:04:14,605 --> 00:04:16,466
There it goes.

25
00:04:31,084 --> 00:04:36,932
Typiskt av armarna som är använda av en nation som har principer för krig som terrorisering och mörkret av kvinnor och barn.

26
00:04:36,951 --> 00:04:40,615
Det pilotlösa flyget eller flygbombet.

27
00:04:40,656 --> 00:04:43,240
Inte ett legitimerat arm med vilket att vinna en krig.

28
00:04:43,259 --> 00:04:45,702
Bara en evig agent av senslös utbrott och skadning.

29
00:04:45,723 --> 00:04:48,826
Lanserad mot civiliseringar av en alldeles förlorad bullen.

30
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:58,235
Efter att ha mött den tragiska historien om Griekenland, så ska vi titta på Kretens äldre.

31
00:04:58,254 --> 00:05:00,276
Det här var en tragedi 1941, men vi har återkommit till Kret.

32
00:05:38,696 --> 00:05:41,778
Within range of German waters the peasants plow their land.

33
00:05:42,358 --> 00:05:45,461
And the peasant often carries an automatic weapon as he plows.

34
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,721
Nearby is a rough cemetery.

35
00:05:46,742 --> 00:05:57,829
There are many British and New Zealand graves on the island of Crete.

36
00:05:59,071 --> 00:06:01,992
That is the district where the Germans are waiting.

37
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,920
Och det här är Athens.

38
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,862
Kameran berättar om en annan grekisk tragedi.

39
00:06:16,982 --> 00:06:23,744
Rivaler i det här balkanska kapitalet ställde sig till att kämpa för kraft efter att den tyska upprättelsen skickades ut.

40
00:06:23,803 --> 00:06:29,987
Och brittiska soldaterna fick döda några av dem för att förhindra större blodlöshet.

41
00:06:30,007 --> 00:06:30,987
Kämpningen fortsätter.

42
00:06:31,107 --> 00:06:36,269
Grekisk politik är mycket för komplicerad för att förbättra lättfärdiga beställningar av rätt eller fel.

43
00:06:36,309 --> 00:06:40,790
Men vi måste ta försäkring från den här upprättelsen att det kan finnas flera skatt, även när Hitlers krig är gjort.

44
00:06:43,591 --> 00:06:51,134
The Allies have been sending food to the starving people of Greece by neutral ships during the German occupation and by our own much needed shipping after.

45
00:06:51,855 --> 00:06:57,858
Strikes of Greek stevedores in the Piraeus prevented the unloading of this relief even while their own women and children starved.

46
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:00,220
But the unloading has since been resumed.

47
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:05,182
There have been divided opinions on the question of which party should govern Greece.

48
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:09,584
There can only be one opinion of those who callously prolong the sufferings of their fellow men.

49
00:07:54,906 --> 00:07:57,567
The British force in Attica has been gaining the upper hand.

50
00:07:58,267 --> 00:08:03,750
And when our soldiers are the masters of Athens, the Greek people will have a chance to choose their own government by peaceful means.

51
00:08:04,711 --> 00:08:10,095
In the meantime, thank God for a British statesman who does what he believes to be right and sticks to it.

52
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:12,677
A statesman who is willing to face the risk of death in order to do his duty.

53
00:08:12,716 --> 00:08:14,937
In the unhappy city of Athens, organized fighting between our troops and the LAS has now ended.

54
00:08:25,322 --> 00:08:31,103
In those parts of the town previously held by the rebels, widespread destruction greets the eyes of civilians returning to their homes.

55
00:08:31,122 --> 00:08:32,683
Street cars damaged in the fighting have to be towed by British lorries.

56
00:08:32,703 --> 00:08:35,504
At large central dumps, captured arms and equipment of the rebel forces is dealt with by our troops.

57
00:08:35,565 --> 00:08:37,664
Angry scenes take place as suspected rebels are brought in by the National Guard.

58
00:08:57,259 --> 00:08:59,039
Life is slowly returning to Athens.

59
00:08:59,059 --> 00:09:02,442
Ships are unloading relief supplies at the Piraeus, soup kitchens are set up and in the streets the people of Athens walk once more without fear.

60
00:09:02,462 --> 00:09:06,666
Attending another meeting is the supreme commander in the Mediterranean, Field Marshal Alexander, seen here on his way to our headquarters.

61
00:09:06,686 --> 00:09:08,226
The commander in chief Greece, General Scobie.

62
00:09:26,015 --> 00:09:32,277
At British GHQ the changing of the guard takes place with parade ground precision before an admiring crowd.

63
00:09:32,297 --> 00:09:46,940
Let us hope that the clouds are finally lifting over Greece and that new happiness will come to our people after their dark and difficult years.

64
00:09:46,980 --> 00:09:54,981
Ärade församling, för andra gången under detta krig går det svenska folket till riksdagsmönnerval i år.

65
00:09:57,014 --> 00:10:00,697
Något avsteg från normal ordning har icke behövt ske.

66
00:10:01,677 --> 00:10:08,022
Detta visar bäst hur väl vi lyckats bevara vår handlingsfrihet och vår demokrati.

67
00:10:09,342 --> 00:10:12,566
Det borde då vara en högtid att gå till val.

68
00:10:12,586 --> 00:10:18,490
1940 uteblev emellertid mer än en miljon väljare.

69
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:21,732
Detta får inte upprepas i år.

70
00:10:22,513 --> 00:10:25,676
Den 17 september måste alla rösta.

71
00:10:26,538 --> 00:10:31,721
Det gäller ju inte blott att bestämma om våra egna inre angelägenheter.

72
00:10:32,361 --> 00:10:41,648
Det gäller också att utåt manifestera det svenska folkets vakenhet och dess levande vilja att bevara sin frihet och sin fred.

73
00:10:42,568 --> 00:10:48,091
Den som senast i fjol fyllde 23 år har rösträtt man som kvinna.

74
00:10:49,211 --> 00:10:51,073
Rösta den 17 september.
